Chicken Tandoori Recipe
Ingredients:
- 1 kg chicken (cut into pieces)
- 1 cup plain yogurt
- 2 tbsp lemon juice
- 2 tbsp ginger-garlic paste
- 2 tsp red chili powder
- 1 tsp turmeric powder
- 2 tsp garam masala
- 1 tsp cumin powder
- 2 tbsp vegetable oil
- Salt to taste
- Fresh coriander and lemon wedges for garnish

Instructions:
1. Make deep cuts in the chicken pieces.
2. In a bowl, mix yogurt, lemon juice, ginger-garlic paste, chili powder, turmeric, garam masala, cumin powder, oil, and salt.
3. Coat the chicken with the marinade. Cover and refrigerate for at least 4 hours (overnight for best results).
4. Preheat oven to 200°C (400°F) or prepare a grill.
5. Place chicken on a rack or grill. Cook for 25-30 minutes, turning halfway, until cooked and slightly charred.
6. Garnish with coriander and lemon wedges. Serve hot.

Enjoy your homemade Chicken Tandoori!